highlights.description: Farold discusses his concern for the lack of diversity and ways to express your culture throughout Madison, specifically at UW-Madison.
Katie continues on with the discussion of lack of cultural expression and diversity in Madison.
Katie expresses her concern for housing availability for minority groups and other individuals that may not conform to community standards.
Katie discusses the importance of doing more than being not racist, but rather being anti racist.
Katie speaks on her hopes for the community in regards to everyone having access to living a quality life.
Justyce discusses reflects on her experiences with resorting to silence and stresses the importance of speaking up when needed.
